# Website form success toast is automatic

## Rule

The website axios layer installs `ResMainMessageMiddleware` (`website/src/resources/configs/axios.ts`) which calls `preMessages.showOrSaveMessages(myInstance, res)` on every response. That helper (`website/src/app/services/pre-messages.ts`) shows **every** `res.messages.main` entry as a toast automatically (or saves them as pre-messages for SSR, shown on browser hydration).

Therefore a form `afterSentSuccess` funnel **must not** manually call `toast.showToast(mainMessage)` for the backend success/error main message — it is already shown, and calling it again produces a **duplicate toast**.

## Required pattern

`afterSentSuccess` should only do side effects the framework does NOT already own: navigation, value reset, adapter reload, reading a payload (e.g. a payment URL). Match the canonical forms:

```ts
await form.d.send({
    sub: "create",
    funnels: {
        afterSentSuccess: async () => {
            nav.back();
        }
    }
});
```

Canonical references: `website/src/app/ui/components/customer/members/CustomerMemberFormScreen.tsx` (`nav.back()` only), `website/src/app/ui/components/customer/hooks/useCustomerNotifications.ts` when present (resets values + reloads, no toast).

## Opt-out is explicit

The framework auto-shows main messages by default. To suppress it for a specific send, pass `autoMainMessage: false` to `d.send(...)` and show your own toast.

## Forbidden

- `await toast.showToast(mainMessage)` / `toast.showToast(res?.data?.mainMessages?.[0])` inside a form `afterSentSuccess` (or `afterSentError`) funnel without `autoMainMessage: false`.
- Keeping a `toast` import in a form screen only for this redundant call.

## Legitimate manual toasts (NOT form main messages)

These are NOT the backend main message and stay manual:

- Social-auth provider failure before `d.send` (`pages/Login.tsx`, `pages/Register.tsx`).
- Network-error fallback in the axios reject handler (`resources/configs/axios.ts`).

